subSubSection.paragraph:
Natural history. Adult specimens have been collected on flowers and foliage of plants in the families Euphorbiaceae (
Croton sp.
), Loganiaceae (
Buddleia cordata Kunth
), Ranunculaceae (
Clematis paucifolia Nutt.
), Rhamnaceae (
Condalia ericoides (A. Gray) M.C. Johnst.
), and Verbenaceae (
Lippia ligustrina (Lag.) Kuntze
).
